<module>
  <title><m>-(a)il</m> adjective-deriving suffix</title>
  <p></p>
  <p><strong>-(a)il</strong> is a suffix used to create <a href="?xx=adjectives/derived_adjectives">derived adjectives</a> from nouns.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>fear</i> <en>man</en> ⇒ <m>fearail</m> <en>manly</en></li>
    <li><i>caraid</i> <en>friend</en> ⇒ <m>càirdeil</m> <en>friendly</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-loinn</i> <en>inelegance</en> ⇒ <m>mì-loinneil</m> <en>inelegant</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-mhodh</i> <en>discourtesy</en> ⇒ <m>mì-mhodhail</m> <en>discourteous, rude</en> (also <i>mìomhail</i>)</li>
    <li><i>mì-rian</i> <en>disorder, confusion</en> ⇒ <m>mì-rianail</m> <en>confusion, disorderly</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-thaing</i> <en>ingratitude</en> ⇒ <m>mì-thaingeil</m> <en>ungrateful</en></li>
    <li><i>slàinte</i> <en>health</en> ⇒ <m>slàinteil</m> <en>sanitary</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>[cf. <xref id="Gillies1902" p="151"/>]</p>
</module>

